{"title":"Bianchi’s new Infinito gets a gravel makeover","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-infinito-2026","date":1772796804000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-infinito-2026\">Bianchi’s new Infinito gets a gravel makeover</a></p>\n\n<p>Bianchi has launched the latest version of its popular Infinito <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-endurance-road-bikes\">endurance bike</a>, with the emphasis on blurring the lines between road bike and gravel bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Infinito was always designed to be about comfort over long distances, and that remit hasn’t changed, but now it has adopted a number of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-bike\">gravel bike</a> elements that make it suitable for off-road jaunts while still remaining at heart a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">road bike</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tyre clearance has increased from 32mm maximum up to 40mm, allowing for the use of gravel tyres, and the frame is set up to accept either 2x or 1x groupsets depending on the rider’s preference.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            \r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-arcadex-al\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/10/bianchi-arcadex-al-red-150x150.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/10/bianchi-arcadex-al-red-150x150.webp 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/10/bianchi-arcadex-al-red-75x75.webp 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/10/bianchi-arcadex-al-red-350x350.webp 350w\" alt=\"bianchi-arcadex-al-red-150x150.webp\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>New Bianchi Arcadex AL is a 'premium aluminium' gravel bike</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/road-bikes/bianchi-specialissima-rc-2024\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/OP_230831_Bianchi_07175-150x150.webp\" alt=\"Bianchi Specialissima 2024\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/OP_230831_Bianchi_07175-150x150.webp 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/OP_230831_Bianchi_07175-75x75.webp 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/OP_230831_Bianchi_07175-350x350.webp 350w\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>New Bianchi Specialissima RC is faster and illegally light</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-all-road-bikes\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/10/canyon-endurace-2023-review-15-150x150.webp\" alt=\"Man riding Canyon Endurace bicycle on gravel road\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/10/canyon-endurace-2023-review-15-150x150.webp 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/10/canyon-endurace-2023-review-15-75x75.webp 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/10/canyon-endurace-2023-review-15-350x350.webp 350w\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>Best all-road bikes 2026 reviewed</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/in-pictures-bianchis-classic-bikes\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/09/02173500/classic_bikes_bianchi_04_disc_brake_chrono_prototype_1-150x150.webp\" alt=\"classic_bikes_bianchi_04_disc_brake_chrono_prototype_1\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/09/02173500/classic_bikes_bianchi_04_disc_brake_chrono_prototype_1-150x150.webp 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/09/02173500/classic_bikes_bianchi_04_disc_brake_chrono_prototype_1-75x75.webp 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/09/02173500/classic_bikes_bianchi_04_disc_brake_chrono_prototype_1-350x350.webp 350w\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>A history of Bianchi's classic bikes</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<div>\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-647x970.jpg 647w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-750x1124.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-1140x1709.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-2-scaled.jpg 1708w\" /><figcaption>There’s a down tube storage hatch dubbed an ’embedded toolbox’. </figcaption><figcaption>Bianchi</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-647x970.jpg 647w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-750x1124.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-1140x1709.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-4-scaled.jpg 1708w\" /><figcaption>The tyre clearance goes beyond all-road into straight-up gravel. </figcaption><figcaption>Bianchi</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>The down tube now sports a storage compartment behind a hatch beneath the bottle cage. Bianchi calls it an ‘embedded toolbox’ and it can hold tools, a pump or a wind jacket without compromising the aerodynamics of the frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Perhaps most significantly, the new Infinito has reintroduced Bianchi’s Countervail vibration damping tech to the carbon layup – something that was missing from the previous model.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Countervail is a viscoelastic material that combines with the carbon fibre in the frame to absorb vibrations to make for a smoother ride and reduce fatigue during long days in the saddle. It’s something that <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/in-pictures-bianchis-classic-bikes\">Bianchi</a> has incorporated into its bikes for a number of years, but the new Infinito showcases the latest version of Countervail, which Bianchi claims is 20% lighter than before and more shock-absorbing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Countervail has also found its way into the seatpost, which has been shaped to allow for more compliance without having to resort to external damping systems that might add weight or unnecessary complexity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Those comfort-inducing elements are balanced by a stiffer-than-before frame and fork, which were developed as a fully integrated system to ensure precise handling under load, and which Bianchi claims provides a 12 watt improvement over the last Infinito.</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"544\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-970x544.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-970x544.png 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-300x168.png 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-768x431.png 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-1536x862.png 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-2048x1149.png 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-750x421.png 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-1-1140x640.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-970x534.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-970x534.png 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-300x165.png 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-768x423.png 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-1536x846.png 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-2048x1127.png 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-750x413.png 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Bianchi-Infinito-Geometry-26-2-1140x628.png 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>There have also been changes to the geometry of the Infinito. Compared to the previous model, the new version has a slightly higher stack and shorter reach, making for a more upright position that prioritises comfort and stability over raciness. The chainstays are also 7mm longer than before (422mm on most sizes, except for the largest frames which are 424mm). This not only helps to accommodate those larger tyres but makes for a more stable ride at speed on rougher ground.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A zero-offset seatpost puts the rider a little further forward over the pedals, the idea being to open the hip angle to improve breathing and pedalling efficiency. The trail is also marginally longer than before by a millimetre, which will make for slightly more predictable handling.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To complement the frame, Bianchi has introduced new RC 49R carbon wheels, engineered by Bianchi’s Reparto Corse, which feature an aerodynamic 49mm rim depth for suitably sporty performance on the road, and a 25mm internal rim width to suit wider tyres.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In terms of looks, the new Infinito is noticeably more fluid than the last model. Where it was previously all straight lines and sharp angles, the new bike is gently curved and softer in appearance. There also appears to be a wider range of colours with more lustrous, shimmering paintjobs on offer (don’t worry, celeste is still an option).</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-647x970.jpg 647w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-1140x1709.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-3-scaled.jpg 1707w\" /><figcaption>While the new Infinito does come in Celeste, there are a range of bright colourways available, including this limited edition white and purple. </figcaption><figcaption>Bianchi</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-647x970.jpg 647w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-750x1124.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-1140x1709.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/bianchi-infinito-26-5-scaled.jpg 1708w\" /><figcaption>There’s a kink in the seatpost to help add compliance without adding a heavy or complex external damping system. </figcaption><figcaption>Bianchi</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>A special colourway of glossy white and purple fade will be available on a limited run of 200 numbered Infinitos as part of the launch celebrations. These bikes will also come with a personalised welcome kit and premium spec.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Infinito will be available in seven frame sizes, ranging from 47cm to 61cm, which should provide a good fit for the majority of riders, however short or tall.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At present, European pricing for the new standard Infinito models starts at €2,790 for a Shimano 105 spec and goes up to €7,790 for the Custom Infinito Pro build and exclusive finish, although we’ve yet to establish prices for the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bianchi CEO Alberto Cavaggioni says, ‘With the new Infinito, we wanted to honour our high-performance racing DNA while fully embracing modern cycling, where a single ride might transition from pristine asphalt to unpredictable light gravel. This is a bike that empowers cyclists to ignore the surface altogether and focus entirely on the pure joy of the ride, allowing them to go further, faster and with more control.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At the time of writing, <em>Cyclist</em> is at the launch event for the new Bianchi Infinito, so we’ll report back with our first impressions in a future article. Watch this space.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>For more information and to find your nearest dealer go to <a href=\"https://www.bianchi.com/store/int_EN/bikes/road/endurance.html\" target=\"_blank\">bianchi.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-infinito-2026\">Bianchi’s new Infinito gets a gravel makeover</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Will Strickson &#124; Website Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"59551f1996289ed55f2a3a8090933e1280592f40e761c09d08a5ceed1550ba73","category":"Cycling"}